description: Blast arrives to lure Stronghold and Livewire back to the Harbinger Foundation -- with the help of the Eternal Warrior?
name: The Price

description: Bloodshot, Geoff and the Eternal Warrior travel to the Balkan Mountains and the Philipines in pursuit of Webnet and the villainous arms dealer, the Weaponeer. Meanwhile, a trap is waiting...
name: Search For The Vault

description: Inside the Weaponeer's secret volcano base, Bloodshot, Geomancer and the Eternal Warrior face an onslaught of Webnet soldiers. Standing against impossible odds and locked inside the belly of the beast, our heroes do what they do best and hijack a submarine!
name: Search And Destroy

This is a special issue where Ember is featured a Queen of the Palace of the High Ones, and every known elf, past, present, & future has gathered in a cosmic reunion of ultimate proportions. Cutter is featured as a wizened hermit, still supported by #leetah in his old age.

Overview

Only Wacky can save Christmas! Wacky's Christmas Special takes him to the North Pole, and Christmas will never be the same again!
name: A Christmas Peril

description:
Overview

Wacky discovers that our precious ozone is being stolen by mysterious aliens and immediately sets out to stop them. What follows is sure to be his wildest adventure yet!
name: The Ozone Bandits

description:
Overview

The Wack is back! Reuniting the team that scripted all those great early Boris stories! Mike Richardson and Randy Stradley team-up with artist Jim Bradrick to bring back the kind of parody the fans are screaming for! This time they take aim at a certain red and blue garbed "Action Ace" who just happens to be celebrating his 50th anniversary this year! Join the celebration!
name: Superwack, Squirrel of Tomorrow

description:
On the run from robots at the Thomas Edison Museum in 2033, Ivar finds himself transported to New York in 1998, where a friend offers a device that may help control his leaps in time. But as Ivar sets off to meet the Wright Brothers a mysterious menace orbits above Earth hell bent on stealing his temporal powers -- and she's got an android!

Time: 1998, 2033, 1918.
name: Mac!

description:
"Escape from New York."

After the events of The Final Days story arc, Frank Castle finds himself in an unusual state. He's now black. Punisher heads to a Chicago safe house to find weapons and money, but he finds bigotry instead. Frank must enlist Cage's help in order to retrieve his stash.

This issue features one pin-up by Mark Bright and Daniel Panosian. The pin-up features Punisher and Power Man.
name: Escape From New York

description:
"Crackdown"

Continuing one of the more bizarre story turns in Punisher history, Punisher's skin color has changed to black after a plastic surgery operation. After residents in a south side Chicago apartment building are being harassed by drug dealers, Punisher and Luke Cage must team up to take them out.
name: Crackdown

description:
"Fade... to White"

The third and final part to the unusual story of Frank Castle being black. With his cover blown by George Wong, Punisher must decide if it is worth continuing in his disguise. Features George Wong from The Final Days arc.

Issue has one pin-up with art by Mark Bright featuring Punisher and Power Man.
name: Fade... To White

description: A run for groceries turns dangerous when masked gunmen take over the entire store. Swift-thinking gets the civilians out the fire-zone but they are still in danger. Frank, lacking in conventional weapons, must use what he finds to take out the criminals and save innocent lives.
name: The Big Check-Out

description:
Frank Castle is in England on the search of Snakebite, a Mercenary working for the Kingpin.

After being attacked by Interpol, Frank is rescued by another Vigilante called Outlaw.

Together they search for Snakebite, Interogating criminals with their vigilante methods until they find him.
name: Eurohit #1: Arrivals

description:
"Eurohit, Part 2 of 7: French Connections"

Punisher tried to take down Snakebite, but is outgunned. Wounded and in Interpol custody, Punisher is momentarily sidelined while Kingpin continues to assert his control over Europe.
name: Eurohit #2: French Connections

description: The Punisher still pursuing Snakebite follows a lead to a resort in Germany hoping to get information their. When Frank arrives the person he wanted to contact is no longer at the resort and the person running it is acting very strange and the resorts guards are carrying automatic weaponry. Frank realizes he might be in a difficult situation here.
name: Eurohit #3: Black Forest Black Bear

description: The Punisher continues going after Snakebite trying to stop the Kingpin from gaining control of all organized crime in Europe.
name: Eurohit #4: Swiss Timing

description:
"Eurohit, Part 5 of 7: Seeing Red"

The Punisher heads to Spain! With the assistance of Tarantula and Morgan Sinclair, Punisher is taken to a Spanish Ranch to inform the owner of Snakebite's plans. While there, the group is ambushed.
name: Eurohit #5: Seeing Red

description: Frank Castle returns to London to devise a plan to stop Kingpin. Assisting his efforts are Morgan Sinclair, Micro, Tarantula, and Outlaw. The Kingpin edges closer to accomplishing his goals, calling for a meeting with various gang leaders he intends to kill.
name: Eurohit #6: Capital Punishment

description:
"Eurohit, 7 of 7: Tunnel Vision"

Punisher and his allies face off against Kingpin and his cronies with the fate of Europe holding in the balance. The Kingpin continues to vie for power in Europe by using his legitimate business dealings to hide his real goal: killing the heads of many of Europe's top gangs in order to take over. While Kingpin weasels away, Snakebite is left behind to deal with Punisher.
name: Eurohit #7: Tunnel Vision

description: Punisher returns to the United States and finds that crime has run rampant during his absence. What's a vigilante to do? Punisher renews his war with vigor in order to show criminals that he's back in town.
name: Loose Ends

description: Punisher goes on a high speed chase against a group of gangsters. The pursuit of the gangsters brings Punisher face to face with a congressman. While saving the congressman's life, he accidentally breaks his wrist. Punisher's actions don't sit well with everyone and lead to the congressman forming VIGIL to hunt down vigilantes.
name: Life During Wartime

description:
"Police Action, Part 1 of 3"

With the new vigilante hunting group VIGIL on the prowl, Punisher must take extra steps to ensure his safety. However, VIGIL surmises his next target and await for Punisher to make his move.
name: Police Action: Part 1

description: The Legion of Super-Heroes are presented to the United Planets in the hope that they will be officially sanctioned. When they save the lives of all the delegates in the meeting, they are granted their sanction. Soon, requests are sent to several planets that are part of the United Planets to acquire representatives for the Legion.
name: Close Encounters

description:
This volume contains the BLACK JACK installments from MANGA VIZION Vol. 3, No. 9 through Vol. 4, No. 3 in their entirety.

A brilliant doctor with a dark secret...

In his highly acclaimed medical drama, world-renowned manga artist Osamu Tezuka plumbs the depths of the human psyche.

Although able to work miracles, due to mysterious circumstances, Doctor Black Jack is unlicensed to practice. Thus, his clientele often harbor some unsavory secrets of their own...

Where's the Doctor?

Black Jack is forced to use the organs of a healthy young man to save the life of the rotten-to-the-core son of a wealthy industrialist.

The Face in the Affliction

Legend mixes with reality when a mysterious stranger begs Black Jack to excise a hideous face growing over his own.

The Teratogenous Cystoma

Black Jack acquires a hot-tempered little assistant from a bizarre source.

The Encounter

Learn the tragic story of Black Jack's long-lost love.

Plus four more mind-boggling tales mixing fact with fiction!

Chapter Titles

  • Operation One: Where's the Doctor!?
  • Operation Two: The Face in the Affliction
  • Operation Three: The Teratogenous Cystoma
  • Operation Four: The Encounter
  • Operation Five: Two Loves
  • Operation Six: Sometimes Like Pearls
  • Operation Seven: To Each His Own
  • Operation Eight: Emergency Shelter

Lying somewhere between medical drama, cartoon humor, and film noir lies Black Jack, the ongoing adventures of an underground doctor who is the last resort for some very unusual patients. In this volume, the risk-taking Black Jack is at the mercy of a doctor after a horrible car wreck.

Empty Graves (8 pages) [Saint]

"It all started out with a public efficiency display..." (6 pages) [Lucky Dale]

"Newspaper sometimes most enlightening...." (2 pages) [Foo Shampoo]

"The snake gave Eve an apple..." (6 pages) [Prop Bowers]

Saint Versus the Sinners (6 pages) [Saint]

The Star Gazer (8 pages) - A woman, convinced that the stars have predicted her death, is reassured by the Saint that this will not occur.

"When Lucky Dale went to visit her uncle..." (6 pages) - When Lucky Dale went to visit her uncle in a sleepy Florida town, she found her quiet stay at the sea shore turned into intrigue involving murder and robbery.

Text Story: Double Trouble (2 pages)

"Backwards or forwards..." (6 pages) - Backwards or forwards, no matter how you spell it, means a barrel-full of grief for flying ace Prop Bowers!

The Saint Meets the Housing Shortage (8 pages) - Distressed over the current housing shortage, the agent for the Mayhew Mansion tells Templar of the disappearance of a soldier from that very mansion, so the Saint decides to visit the mansion and talk to the G.I.'s wife. Some think ghosts haunt the mansion....but the Saint discovers otherwise!
name: The Star Gazer
